WORLD CORPORATE INSURANCE REPORT via NewsNet
January 12, 1996

INDEPENDENT/LA PALATINE

Aachener und Munchener Beteiligungs-AG, Aachen, has finally managed to
rid itself of La Palatine Assurance SA, Suresnes, the source of much
distress for another of its more recent disposals, Aachener
Ruckversicherungs-Ges AG (Aachen Re), Aachen.  Independent Insurance
Holdings Ltd, a subsidiary of Independent Insurance Group plc, London,
has taken over Palatine from Groupement Francais d'Assurances IARD
(GFA), Suresnes.  GFA was a subsidiary of the old Aachen Re, which has
now been renamed AM Konzernruckversicherung AG after being transformed
into a purely in-house reinsurer.

GFA has transferred a major portion of its business to Palatine and
sold this business with the company.  Palatine has been active in the
French personal lines market since 1990 and has mainly sold motor,
property and accident policies via brokers and multiple agents.  The
net assets of Palatine were worth Fr35m (US$7.1m) on transfer to
Independent, which secured guarantees particularly regarding reserve
adequacy and Fr140m in order to restructure Palatine.



