<A NAME = "32"></A>Copyright
WORLD CORPORATE INSURANCE REPORT via NewsNet
January 12, 1996

UK P&I

Members of the United Kingdom Mutual Steam Ship Assurance Association
Bermuda Ltd (UK P&I Club), Hamilton, have voted overwhelmingly in
favour of the International Group of P&I Club's proposal to limit each
member's liability to pay catastrophe calls to 20% of an owner's
limitation fund for property damage claims under the 1976 Limitation
Convention.  This will result in a potential total claim on all members
in the International Group of between US$18bn and $20bn.  It must be
accepted by a minimum of ten clubs in the International Group,
representing at least 85% of International Group's tonnage.  According
to the UK Club, a number of other clubs are holding meetings of members
along the same lines, with a representative picture of shipowners'
views hopefully becoming apparent by the end of January.  The
proposals, if approved by all members of the group, will be adopted for
the policy year commencing 20 February.



<A HREF ="#HeadList">Back to Headline List</A><BR>
