WORLD INSURANCE REPORT via NewsNet
January 12, 1996

WINDSTORM MARKET ASSISTANCE PROPOSAL

Acting New Jersey insurance commissioner Elizabeth Randall said she
intended to create a windstorm market assistance programme to improve
the availability of insurance for homeowners on the NJ coast, she told
the New Jersey Senate judiciary committee.  "If a co-operative,
voluntary effort by the industry fails to achieve the desired result, I
am prepared to consider moving forward with a regulatory approach on
behalf of our citizens," she said.  Her proposal would involve insurers
assuming liability in rotation for underwriting cover for homeowners
unable to obtain it.



