January 12, 1996

LLOYD'S TO SCRAP HARDSHIP SCHEME

Lloyd's will scrap the hardship scheme from the end of February,
replacing it by assistance negotiated on an individual basis with the
Financial Recovery Department.  As of November 1995, 1,066 hardship
scheme proposals had been accepted and 906 applications were being
processed.  The Association of Lloyd's Members (ALM) expressed anxiety
about the decision, on which it was not consulted.



