Philippines:  heavy rainfall led to flash floods, Davao City, 600 miles
S Manila.  Parts of city under five feet of water.  9 dead, 3 missing.

19.12.95, bad weather, property damage, fatalities

South Africa:  torrential rain led to flooding, Eastern Transvaal.  At
least 6 dead.

19.12.95, earthquake, property damage, fatalities

Guatemala:  earthquake, measuring Richter 5.3, lasting nine seconds,
epicentre app 50 miles N Guatemala City, struck app 1456 local.
Several houses damaged and road destroyed.  1 dead, at least 1 injured.

20.12.95, earthquake, fatalities

Indonesia:  earthquake, measuring Richter 5.5, epicentre 110km NE
Wamena, struck app 0823 local, causing landslides in at least 10
villages, Kurima sub-district.  4 dead.

25.12.95, bad weather, property damage

Jamaica:  overnight showers led to flooding, Ocho Rios, St Ann.  Motor
vehicles swept away, homes flooded, cables and underground pipes
uprooted, road surfaces eroded.  Preliminary est damage: US$50m.

23.12.95, bad weather, property damage

UK:  blizzards and winds up to 100mph damaged power lines, blocking
roads, northern Scotland (see story p?).  Power supplies cut to 000's
of homes, Scotland, and all roads closed on Shetland Islands.  Drifts
up to 30-ft high, transport disrupted.  Shetland Islands declared state
of emergency.

27.12.95, bad weather, property damage, fatalities

Philippines:  heavy rains triggered flooding and landslides, Cagayan,
Isabela, Quirino, Nueva Vizcaya and Aurora provinces.  Some 442 houses
damaged or destroyed.  Est damage to crops and infrastructure put at
Pesos13m (US$500,000).  President declared Aurora under state of
calamity and released Pesos1m (US$38,461) in aid.  At least 13 dead, 3
missing.

27.12.95, bad weather, property damage

Albania:  heavy rain led to widespread flooding, north-western areas.
More than 5,000 hectares land submerged, 00's of houses destroyed,
Snkodra, Malesi e Madhe, Lezhe and Kruja districts.

27.12.95, bad weather, flooding, fatalities

South Africa:  heavy seasonal rains caused R Umsunduzi and Slangspruit
tributary to burst their banks, causing flash floods, Pietermaritzburg
and surrounding region, KwaZulu-Natal province.  At least 166 dead.
(28.12) National disaster area declared.  Central govt to match R1m
(US$278,000) in aid granted by provincial administration.

30.12.95, bad weather, fatalities

Brazil:  heavy rainstorms led to floods and landslides, southern and
east-central areas.  App 1,000 homes washed away plus bridges and
stretches of highway, Santa Catarina state  At least 61 dead, 31
missing.

1.1.96, earthquake, fatalities

Indonesia:  earthquake, measuring Richter 7, epicentre Celebes Sea, app
125km N Palu, Sulawesi island, triggered tidal waves of 1.5 metres.  At
least 384 wooden houses and government buildings damaged.  Earthquake
led to tidal wave, Sulawest island, left 8 dead, flooding, Sumatera,
left 16 dead.

3.1.96, bad weather, property damage, fatalities

Indonesia:  several days of rain triggered flooding, northern Aceh
province, Sumatra.  Up to 190 villages, rice fields, palm plantations
and coffee growing areas flooded, 000's made homeless, Rantau oil field
shut down.  At least 18 dead, 9 missing.  Est losses, including
livestock, Aceh Province, put at US$87m.  (6.1) flooding spread to
western part of Java island, destroying app 2,871 hectares of paddy
fields and affecting more than 4,000 houses and schools in 13 villages.
 (9.1) heavy rains caused R Ciliwung to overflow, flooding tens of
thousands of homes, central, east and south Jakarta.  At least 11 dead.

3.1.96, bad weather, property damage

US:  tornado, accompanying thunderstorm, damaged 100 homes, overturned
cars and left app 20,000 homes without electricity, Dade County, app 12
miles S Miami FL, app 0810 local.

4.1.96, bad weather, property damage, fatalities

CIS:  Kazakhstan:  two weeks of blizzards caused est damage of
Tenge200m (US$3m).  Electricity and telephone lines, several buildings
damaged.  113 dead, 5 missing.

4.1.96, bad weather, property damage

Romania:  melting snow and rain flooded 25 districts, washed away app
4,000 houses, north-western areas.  Est damage put at more than Lei10bn
(US$3.4m).

7.1.96, snowstorm, fatalities

US:  snowstorm, "largest in at least two years", swept across eastern
US, leading to closure of airports in Washington, Boston, New York, and
Philadelphia, businesses and schools.  000's flights cancelled.  Up to
24 inches of snow fell, Washington DC, with winds gusting up to 40mph.
App 30 inches of snow fell, Philadelphia area.  State of emergency
declared, New York and Boston, plus at least eight north-eastern
states.  Up to 20-30 inches snow fell, Appalachian mountains, West
Virginia.  App 80 dead.  Airlines expect blizzard costs to run into
"millions of dollars".  (9.1) Pennsylvania governor est costs to state
businesses at "hundreds of millions of dollars" and cost to area state
and local government "in the millions".  (10.1)  Economic damage est at
between US$5bn and US$10bn.



